HEADWORD: Antecommunion
<hw>An`te*com*mun"ion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A name
given to that part of the Anglican liturgy for the communion, which
precedes the consecration of the elements.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antecursor</ent>⟦br⟧
